div2.p:
"No, thank you," said she. Not that she did not need help;
                        but she wished no disagreeable scene with the workingman's wife who
                        might open the door as they passed his family's flat.

Susan colored painfully—and Palmer, the sensitive, colored also. But
                        he had the tact that does not try to repair a blunder by making a worse one;
                        he pretended not to see Susan's crimson flush.
